    <hard>
        <question>
            <text>For a reaction R -> P, half-life is 100 s when [R]0=1M and 50 s when [R]0=2M. The order is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Zero</option><option id="B">First</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>t1/2 proportional to conc implies zero order.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>For a reaction R -> P, half-life is 100 s when [R]0=1M and 100 s when [R]0=2M. The order is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">First</option><option id="B">Zero</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>t1/2 independent of conc implies first order.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>A first order reaction has k = 0.005 min^-1. If [R]0 = 0.1M, conc after 200 min is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">0.0368 M</option><option id="B">0.05 M</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>[R] = 0.1 * e^(-0.005 * 200) = 0.1 * e^-1 = 0.0368.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Ratio of t(75%) to t(50%) for a first order reaction is exactly ____.</text>
            <option id="A">2</option><option id="B">1.5</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>75% completion is 2 half-lives.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Ratio of t(87.5%) to t(50%) for a first order reaction is exactly ____.</text>
            <option id="A">3</option><option id="B">4</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>87.5% completion is 3 half-lives.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If rate doubles when temp rises from 300K to 310K, Ea is approx ____.</text>
            <option id="A">53.6 kJ/mol</option><option id="B">100 kJ/mol</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>log 2 = (Ea / 2.303 * 8.314) * (10 / 93000).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Decomposition of N2O5 follows first order. If k = 3.4 * 10^-5 s^-1, time for 50% decay? ____.</text>
            <option id="A">20382 s</option><option id="B">10000 s</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>t1/2 = 0.693 / (3.4 * 10^-5).</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>In a reaction mechanism, the sum of molecularities of all steps is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Meaningless</option><option id="B">Overall order</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Molecularity is per step property.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>If a reaction is zero order with respect to R, it must be ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Complex</option><option id="B">Elementary</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
